article.headline: Gardner-Webb 91, Radford 71
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Aaron Linn scored a team-high 22 points and was one of six Gardner-Webb players to score in double figues in a 91-71 win against Radford in the Big South Conference opener for both teams on Thursday night. Nate Blank scored 14 points, Grayson Flittner and Takayo Siddle added 12 apiece and Jonathan Moore and Joshua Henley chipped in 10 each for the Runnin' Bulldogs (2-4, 1-0). Linn was 2-for-2 from beyond the 3-point arc and 4-for-4 from the free-throw line for Gardner-Webb, which shot 52.2 percent (36 of 69) for the game. The Runnin' Bulldogs shot a blistering 22-for-33 from the field in the second half en route to victory. Kenny Thomas scored a game-high 25 points, including hitting five 3-pointers, to lead the Highlanders (2-4, 0-1). Joey Lynch-Flohr added 20 points in the loss.
